## Dependency Injection Wiring (container.ts)

The `ApplicationContainer` class is the wiring hub. It instantiates all services and controllers:

```
ApplicationContainer
  ├── adminAuthService          (no deps)
  ├── adminService              (no deps)
  ├── paymentGatewayService     (no deps)
  ├── productService            (no deps)
  ├── whatsAppService           (no deps — accepts optional Axios instance for testability)
  ├── orderService              (depends on: paymentGatewayService, whatsAppService)
  ├── adminAuthController       (depends on: adminAuthService)
  ├── adminController           (depends on: adminService, productService)
  ├── healthController          (no deps)
  ├── orderController           (depends on: orderService)
  └── webhookController         (depends on: orderService)
```

The container is passed to `createRouter()` which wires each route to its controller method.

---

## API Routes (All prefixed with `/api`)

| Method | Path | Auth | Controller Method | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|-------------------|---------|
| GET | `/health` | No | `healthController.getHealth` | Health check |
| POST | `/orders` | No | `orderController.createOrder` | Manual order creation (returns 201) |
| GET | `/webhooks/whatsapp` | No | `webhookController.verifyWhatsAppWebhook` | WhatsApp webhook verification challenge |
| POST | `/webhooks/whatsapp` | No | `webhookController.handleWhatsAppWebhook` | Incoming WhatsApp messages (returns 200, errors → 500) |
| POST | `/webhooks/payment` | No | `webhookController.handlePaymentWebhook` | Payment gateway callbacks (returns 200, errors → 400) |
| POST | `/admin/auth/login` | No | `adminAuthController.login` | Admin login (returns Set-Cookie header, 401 on bad creds) |
| POST | `/admin/auth/logout` | No | `adminAuthController.logout` | Admin logout (clears cookie via Max-Age=0) |
| GET | `/admin/auth/me` | Cookie or API Key | `adminAuthController.me` | Verify session is still valid (returns 200 or 401 via middleware) |
| GET | `/admin/orders` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.listOrders` | List orders (query: `status`, `paymentStatus`, `search`) |
| GET | `/admin/orders/:orderReference` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.getOrder` | Get single order (404 if missing) |
| PATCH | `/admin/orders/:orderReference/status` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.updateOrderStatus` | Update order status (body: `status`, `note?`) |
| GET | `/admin/payments` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.listPayments` | List payments (query: `status`) |
| GET | `/admin/products` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.listProducts` | List all products |
| POST | `/admin/products` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.createProduct` | Create product (409 if duplicate catalogProductId) |
| PATCH | `/admin/products/:productId` | Cookie or API Key | `adminController.updateProduct` | Update product (404 if missing, 409 if duplicate) |

---

## MongoDB Models

### Order (`orders` collection)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `orderReference` | String | Required, unique, indexed. Format: `ORD-{Date.now()}-{0-999}` |
| `customerName` | String | Default: `"WhatsApp Customer"` |
| `whatsappNumber` | String | Required, indexed |
| `sourceMessageId` | String | Optional, from WhatsApp message `id` field |
| `productName` | String | Default: `"Catalog Product"` |
| `catalogProductId` | String | Optional, links to WhatsApp catalog |
| `quantity` | Number | Min 1, default 1 |
| `totalAmount` | Number | Required, min 0 |
| `currency` | String | Required, default `"PKR"` |
| `status` | Enum | `pending_payment` → `payment_received` → `confirmed` → `processing` → `failed` |
| `paymentStatus` | Enum | `pending`, `paid`, `failed` |
| `paymentLink` | String | Generated Easypaisa payment URL (set after order creation) |
| `paymentGatewayReference` | String | Indexed, set when payment webhook arrives |
| `history` | Array of `{ status, note, changedAt }` | Embedded sub-documents (no `_id` on sub-docs) |
| `createdAt` / `updatedAt` | Date | Auto timestamps |

### Payment (`payments` collection)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `orderReference` | String | Required, indexed |
| `gatewayReference` | String | Indexed, from payment gateway |
| `amount` | Number | Required, min 0. Falls back to order's `totalAmount`, then `rawPayload.amount`, then 0 |
| `currency` | String | Required, default `"PKR"` |
| `status` | Enum | `pending`, `paid`, `failed` (indexed) |
| `rawPayload` | Mixed | Full webhook payload from payment gateway (stored as-is) |
| `createdAt` / `updatedAt` | Date | Auto timestamps |

### Product (`products` collection)

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| `name` | String | Required, trimmed |
| `description` | String | Default `""` |
| `catalogProductId` | String | Unique (sparse), indexed. Sparse allows multiple `null` values |
| `price` | Number | Required, min 0 |
| `currency` | String | Required, default `"PKR"` |
| `stockQuantity` | Number | Required, min 0, default 0 |
| `isActive` | Boolean | Required, default `false`, indexed |
| `createdAt` / `updatedAt` | Date | Auto timestamps |

---

## Shared Types (backend/src/types/order.ts)

```typescript
OrderStatus   = "pending_payment" | "payment_received" | "confirmed" | "processing" | "failed"
PaymentStatus = "pending" | "paid" | "failed"
OrderHistoryEntry = { status: string; note: string; changedAt: Date }
```

---

## Core Flows

### Flow 1: App Startup

```
STANDALONE MODE (server.ts):
  server.ts
    → config/database.ts: mongoose.connect(MONGODB_URI)  ← connects once, persists
    → app.ts: createApp()
        → new ApplicationContainer()                     ← wires all services & controllers
        → new Express app
        → express.json() middleware
        → createRouter(container)                        ← mounts all 15 routes at /api
        → express.static("../frontend/dist") at /admin   ← serves React SPA in production
    → app.listen(port)

VERCEL SERVERLESS MODE (api/index.ts):
  api/index.ts exports handler function
    → On first cold start: mongoose.connect() + createApp() → caches app instance
    → On subsequent warm requests: reuses cached app (no reconnect)
    → vercel.json routes all requests (/(.*)) to this single handler
```

### Flow 2: WhatsApp Order → Payment Link → Payment → Confirmation

This is the **PRIMARY** business flow of the entire app.

```
STEP 1: Customer sends a message on WhatsApp
─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Customer types an order message or taps an interactive button in WhatsApp
      ↓
  WhatsApp Cloud API forwards the message to your webhook URL


STEP 2: Your webhook receives and processes the message
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  POST /api/webhooks/whatsapp
      ↓
  ┌─ WebhookController.handleWhatsAppWebhook(req, res) ──────────────────┐
  │  Wraps in try/catch: returns 200 on success, 500 on error            │
  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
      ↓
  OrderService.handleWhatsAppWebhook(body)
      │
      ├── extractMessageChanges(body)
      │     Traverses: body.entry[]?.changes[]?.value
      │     Uses flatMap + filter to extract all WhatsAppMessageValue objects
      │     Handles missing/undefined safely with optional chaining
      │
      └── For each message value: processMessageValue(value)
            │
            ├── 1. Guard: if (!firstMessage?.from) return early (no sender)
            │
            ├── 2. Extract customer info:
            │       customerName   = contacts[0]?.profile?.name ?? "WhatsApp Customer"
            │       whatsappNumber = messages[0].from                          ← required
            │       sourceMessageId = messages[0].id
            │
            ├── 3. Extract product info (falls through multiple sources):
            │       productName = button_reply?.title                     ← interactive button
            │                   ?? text?.body                             ← plain text message
            │                   ?? "Catalog Product"                      ← fallback default
            │       catalogProductId = order?.product_items[0]?.product_retailer_id
            │                        ?? order?.catalog_id
            │       quantity = order?.product_items[0]?.quantity ?? 1
            │       totalAmount = DEFAULT_AMOUNT × quantity               ← from env
            │
            ├── 4. createOrder(input)
            │       → OrderModel.create({
            │           orderReference: "ORD-{Date.now()}-{Math.random()×1000}",
            │           customerName, whatsappNumber, sourceMessageId,
            │           productName, catalogProductId, quantity, totalAmount,
            │           currency: env.payment.defaultCurrency,
            │           status: "pending_payment",
            │           paymentStatus: "pending",
            │           history: [{
            │             status: "pending_payment",
            │             note: "Order created from WhatsApp webhook.",
            │             changedAt: new Date()
            │           }]
            │         })
            │
            ├── 5. attachPaymentLink(order)
            │       → PaymentGatewayService.createPaymentLink({ orderRef, amount, currency })
            │         (see "Payment Gateway Integration" section below)
            │       → OrderModel.findOneAndUpdate(
            │           { orderReference },
            │           { paymentLink: url },
            │           { new: true }
            │         )
            │       → Returns updated order (or original if update failed)
            │
            └── 6. WhatsAppService.sendTextMessage(to, body)
                  → POST https://graph.facebook.com/{apiVersion}/{phoneNumberId}/messages
                  → Headers: Authorization: Bearer {WHATSAPP_TOKEN}
                  → Body: {
                      messaging_product: "whatsapp",
                      to: whatsappNumber,
                      type: "text",
                      text: {
                        body: "Thank you {name}. Your order {ref} has been created. Payment link: {url}"
                      }
                    }
                  → Message sent as single joined string (3 parts separated by space)


STEP 3: Customer pays via Easypaisa
─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Customer clicks the payment link → completes payment on Easypaisa's page
      ↓
  Easypaisa sends a callback POST to your webhook


STEP 4: Your payment webhook processes the callback
─────────────────────────────────────────────

  POST /api/webhooks/payment
      ↓
  ┌─ WebhookController.handlePaymentWebhook(req, res) ─────────────────┐
  │  Wraps in try/catch: returns 200 on success, 400 on error         │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
      ↓
  OrderService.handlePaymentWebhook(body)
      │
      ├── 1. Extract fields (tries multiple possible field names):
      │       orderReference = body.orderReference
      │                     ?? body.orderRef
      │                     ?? body.merchantOrderId
      │                     ?? ""              ← stringified
      │       gatewayRef     = body.transactionId
      │                     ?? body.txnRefNo
      │                     ?? body.paymentId
      │                     ?? ""              ← stringified
      │       paymentStatus  = (body.paymentStatus ?? body.status ?? "").toLowerCase()
      │
      ├── 2. Guard: if (!orderReference) → throw Error (caught by controller → 400)
      │
      ├── 3. IF paymentStatus IS NOT "paid" AND IS NOT "success":
      │     ┌─ FAILED PAYMENT PATH ───────────────────────────────────────┐
      │     │                                                             │
      │     │  a. recordPayment({ status: "failed", ... })                │
      │     │       → Looks up Order to get amount & currency             │
      │     │       → PaymentModel.create({                               │
      │     │           orderReference, gatewayReference,                 │
      │     │           amount: order?.totalAmount                        │
      │     │                   ?? rawPayload.amount ?? 0,                │
      │     │           currency: order?.currency ?? defaultCurrency,     │
      │     │           status: "failed",                                 │
      │     │           rawPayload: body                                  │
      │     │         })                                                  │
      │     │                                                             │
      │     │  b. updateOrderStatus(orderRef, "failed", "failed",         │
      │     │        "Payment failed or was not completed.",              │
      │     │        gatewayRef)                                          │
      │     │       → OrderModel.findOneAndUpdate(                        │
      │     │           { orderReference },                               │
      │     │           {                                                 │
      │     │             status: "failed",                               │
      │     │             paymentStatus: "failed",                        │
      │     │             paymentGatewayReference: gatewayRef,            │
      │     │             $push: { history: { status, note, changedAt } } │
      │     │           },                                                │
      │     │           { new: true }                                     │
      │     │         )                                                   │
      │     │                                                             │
      │     │  Returns the updated order. NO WhatsApp message sent.       │
      │     └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
      │
      └── 4. IF paymentStatus IS "paid" OR "success":
            ┌─ SUCCESSFUL PAYMENT PATH ───────────────────────────────────┐
            │                                                             │
            │  a. recordPayment({ status: "paid", ... })                  │
            │       → PaymentModel.create({ ...same fields, status: "paid" })
            │                                                             │
            │  b. updateOrderStatus(orderRef, "payment_received", "paid", │
            │        "Payment received from gateway webhook.", gatewayRef)│
            │                                                             │
            │  c. If order found:                                         │
            │       WhatsAppService.sendTextMessage(                      │
            │         whatsappNumber,                                     │
            │         "Payment received for order {ref}."                 │
            │       )                                                     │
            │                                                             │
            │  d. updateOrderStatus(orderRef, "confirmed", "paid",        │
            │        "Order confirmed automatically after payment.")      │
            │                                                             │
            │  e. If order found:                                         │
            │       WhatsAppService.sendTextMessage(                      │
            │         whatsappNumber,                                     │
            │         "Order confirmed. We are preparing {productName}    │
            │          for delivery or processing."                       │
            │       )                                                     │
            │                                                             │
            │  f. updateOrderStatus(orderRef, "processing", "paid",       │
            │        "Order moved to processing.")                        │
            │                                                             │
            │  g. If order found:                                         │
            │       WhatsAppService.sendTextMessage(                      │
            │         whatsappNumber,                                     │
            │         "Delivery or processing update: your order {ref}    │
            │          is now in progress."                               │
            │       )                                                     │
            │                                                             │
            │  Returns the "confirmed" order.                             │
            │  ★ Each status transition is sequential (awaited).          │
            │  ★ Each WhatsApp send is gated: only sends if the           │
            │    previous status update found the order.                  │
            │  ★ This means 3 separate WhatsApp messages after payment.  │
            └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Flow 3: Order Status Lifecycle

```
                         Customer sends WhatsApp message
                                   │
                                   ▼
                         ┌──────────────────┐
                         │  pending_payment  │  ← Order created, payment link generated & sent
                         └────────┬─────────┘
                                  │
                         Payment webhook received
                                  │
                   ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐
                   │ failed/other                 │ "paid" or "success"
                   ▼                              ▼
             ┌──────────┐              ┌──────────────────┐
             │  failed   │              │ payment_received  │  ← WhatsApp: "Payment received for order {ref}"
             └──────────┘              └────────┬─────────┘
              (no message sent)                 │
                                                ▼
                                      ┌──────────────────┐
                                      │    confirmed      │  ← WhatsApp: "Order confirmed. Preparing {product}..."
                                      └────────┬─────────┘
                                                │
                                                ▼
                                      ┌──────────────────┐
                                      │   processing      │  ← WhatsApp: "Order {ref} is now in progress."
                                      └──────────────────┘

  What happens at each state change:
    → Order.status field updated
    → Order.paymentStatus field updated (on payment webhook transitions)
    → Order.paymentGatewayReference set (on payment webhook transitions)
    → Order.history[] gets a new { status, note, changedAt } entry via $push
    → WhatsApp notification sent to customer (except on "failed")
    → Each status update uses findOneAndUpdate with { new: true }
```

### Flow 4: Manual Order Creation (API)

```
  External system / API client / Postman
      │
      ▼
  POST /api/orders
  Body: {
    customerName: string,        ← required
    whatsappNumber: string,      ← required
    productName: string,         ← required
    catalogProductId?: string,
    quantity?: number,           ← defaults to 1
    totalAmount?: number         ← defaults to env.payment.defaultAmount
  }
      │
      ▼
  OrderController.createOrder(req, res)
    → Calls OrderService.createFromManualInput(req.body)
      → Returns 201 { success: true, data: order }
      │
      ▼
  OrderService.createFromManualInput(input)
      │
      ├── quantity    = input.quantity ?? 1
      ├── totalAmount = input.totalAmount ?? env.payment.defaultAmount
      ├── orderReference = buildOrderReference()  → "ORD-{Date.now()}-{random 0-999}"
      │
      ├── createOrder({ ...input, orderReference, quantity, totalAmount,
      │                 currency: env.payment.defaultCurrency })
      │     → OrderModel.create({ status: "pending_payment", paymentStatus: "pending",
      │                          history: [{ status: "pending_payment",
      │                                      note: "Order created from WhatsApp webhook.",
      │                                      changedAt: new Date() }] })
      │
      └── attachPaymentLink(order)
            → PaymentGatewayService.createPaymentLink(...)
            → OrderModel.findOneAndUpdate({ orderReference }, { paymentLink }, { new: true })
            → Returns updated order

  ★ NOTE: Manual order creation does NOT send a WhatsApp message.
    Only orders from WhatsApp webhooks get the payment link sent via WhatsApp.
```

### Flow 5: Admin Authentication

```
═══ LOGIN ═══

  Browser → POST /api/admin/auth/login
  Body: { username, password }
      │
      ▼
  AdminAuthController.login(req, res)
      │
      ├── AdminAuthService.validateCredentials(username, password)
      │     → Guard: if (!env.app.adminPassword) return false
      │                (prevents login when password is not configured)
      │     → crypto.timingSafeEqual(username, env.app.adminUsername)
      │     → crypto.timingSafeEqual(password, env.app.adminPassword)
      │     → All comparisons use constant-time to prevent timing attacks
      │
      ├── (if invalid) → 401 { success: false, message: "Invalid credentials" }
      │
      └── (if valid):
            │
            ├── AdminAuthService.createSessionToken(username)
            │     → payload = { username, expiresAt: Date.now() + 28800000 }  ← 8 hours
            │     → encoded  = Buffer.from(JSON.stringify(payload)).toString("base64url")
            │     → signature = HMAC-SHA256(ADMIN_SESSION_SECRET, encoded)
            │                    .digest("base64url")
            │     → returns "{encoded}.{signature}"
            │
            ├── AdminAuthService.createCookie(token)
            │     → Set-Cookie string:
            │         admin_session={token}; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax; Path=/; Max-Age=28800
            │         + "; Secure" if NODE_ENV === "production"
            │
            └── Response: 200 { success: true, data: { username } }
                + res.setHeader("Set-Cookie", cookie)


═══ SESSION CHECK (every protected request) ═══

  Browser → GET /api/admin/orders (or any admin route)
  Cookie: admin_session={token}
      │
      ▼
  requireAdminAuth middleware runs FIRST:
      │
      ├── 1. Try cookie auth:
      │       sessionToken = AdminAuthService.extractCookie(req.header("cookie"))
      │         → Parses "Cookie" header string
      │         → Splits by ";", trims each
      │         → Finds cookie starting with "admin_session="
      │         → Extracts value after "admin_session="
      │       AdminAuthService.verifySessionToken(sessionToken)
      │         → Splits at ".": [encodedPayload, signature]
      │         → Guard: if either part missing or signatures don't match → false
      │         → Recomputes HMAC-SHA256(secret, encodedPayload).digest("base64url")
      │         → crypto.timingSafeEqual(computed, provided)
      │         → Decodes payload: JSON.parse(Buffer.from(encoded, "base64url").toString("utf8"))
      │         → Verifies: payload.username === env.app.adminUsername
      │         → Verifies: payload.expiresAt > Date.now()
      │         → Returns true/false
      │
      ├── 2. Try API key auth (fallback):
      │       apiKey = req.header("x-admin-api-key")
      │       AdminAuthService.validateApiKey(apiKey)
      │         → Guard: env.app.adminApiKey must be set AND apiKey must be truthy
      │         → crypto.timingSafeEqual(apiKey, env.app.adminApiKey)
      │
      ├── If EITHER method passes → next()  (proceed to controller)
      │
      └── If BOTH fail → 401 { success: false, error: "Admin authentication required." }

  After middleware passes, the controller runs:
      ▼
  AdminAuthController.me(req, res)
    → Response: 200 { success: true }


═══ LOGOUT ═══

  Browser → POST /api/admin/auth/logout
      │
      ▼
  AdminAuthController.logout(req, res)
      → AdminAuthService.clearCookie()
          → Set-Cookie: admin_session=; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax; Path=/; Max-Age=0
          → ★ NOTE: clearCookie does NOT include Secure flag (unlike createCookie)
      → Response: 200 { success: true }


═══ API KEY AUTH (server-to-server) ═══

  External service → Any admin route
  Header: x-admin-api-key: {key}
      │
      ▼
  requireAdminAuth middleware:
    → AdminAuthService.validateApiKey(apiKey)
        → Requires BOTH env.app.adminApiKey to be configured AND apiKey header present
        → crypto.timingSafeEqual() comparison
    → If valid, bypasses cookie check entirely
```

### Flow 6: Admin Panel Operations (with exact DB queries)

```
  ┌─ FRONTEND ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  React App (Vite dev: localhost:5173)                               │
  │  Vite proxy: /api → http://localhost:5000                           │
  │  Axios: baseURL="/api", withCredentials=true (sends cookies)        │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                                    │
                                    ▼
  ┌─ BACKEND ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  requireAdminAuth middleware (cookie or API key)                     │
  │  Controller → Service → Mongoose Model → MongoDB                    │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


  ═══ DASHBOARD (OverviewPage) ═══

    Mount → 3 parallel GET requests:
      GET /api/admin/orders     → AdminService.listOrders()
      GET /api/admin/products   → ProductService.listProducts()
      GET /api/admin/payments   → AdminService.listPayments()

    Displays 6 metric cards:
      ├── Total orders        → orders.length
      ├── Paid orders (green) → orders.filter(o => o.paymentStatus === "paid").length
      ├── Pending (amber)     → orders.filter(o => o.paymentStatus === "pending").length
      ├── Published products  → products.filter(p => p.isActive).length
      ├── Payments count      → payments.length
      └── Paid amount (green) → sum of payments.filter(p => p.status === "paid").amount


  ═══ ORDER MANAGEMENT (OrdersPage) ═══

    GET /api/admin/orders?status=X&paymentStatus=Y&search=Z
      → AdminService.listOrders({ status, paymentStatus, search })
        Builds MongoDB query:
          query.status = filters.status           ← exact match if provided
          query.paymentStatus = filters.paymentStatus  ← exact match if provided
          query.$or = [                           ← case-insensitive regex OR search
            { orderReference: /search/i },
            { customerName: /search/i },
            { whatsappNumber: /search/i }
          ]                                        ← only if search is provided
        → OrderModel.find(query).sort({ createdAt: -1 }).exec()

    PATCH /api/admin/orders/:orderReference/status
      Body: { status: "confirmed"|"processing"|..., note?: string }
      → AdminService.updateOrderStatus(orderRef, status, note)
        Default note: "Order updated from admin panel."
        → OrderModel.findOneAndUpdate(
            { orderReference },
            {
              status,
              $push: {
                history: { status, note, changedAt: new Date() }
              }
            },
            { new: true }
          ).exec()
        → Returns updated order or null → controller returns 404 if null

    ★ NOTE: Admin status updates only change `status`, NOT `paymentStatus`.
      The payment webhook is the only path that changes paymentStatus.


  ═══ PRODUCT MANAGEMENT (ProductsPage) ═══

    GET /api/admin/products
      → ProductService.listProducts()
        → ProductModel.find().sort({ createdAt: -1 }).exec()

    POST /api/admin/products
      Body: { name, catalogProductId?, price, stockQuantity, description?, isActive }
      → ProductService.createProduct(input)
        → ensureUniqueCatalogProductId(input.catalogProductId)
            → If catalogProductId provided:
                ProductModel.findOne({ catalogProductId }).select("_id").exec()
                If found → throw DuplicateProductCatalogIdError → 409
        → ProductModel.create({
            ...input,
            currency: input.currency ?? env.payment.defaultCurrency,
            stockQuantity: input.stockQuantity ?? 0,
            isActive: input.isActive ?? false
          })
        → Returns 201

    PATCH /api/admin/products/:productId
      Body: { name?, catalogProductId?, price?, stockQuantity?, description?, isActive? }
      → ProductService.updateProduct(productId, input)
        → ensureUniqueCatalogProductId(input.catalogProductId, productId)
            → Excludes current product from uniqueness check
        → ProductModel.findByIdAndUpdate(productId, input, {
            new: true,
            runValidators: true
          }).exec()
        → If null → 404
        → If DuplicateProductCatalogIdError → 409
        → Otherwise → 200


  ═══ PAYMENT LISTING (PaymentsPage) ═══

    GET /api/admin/payments?status=paid
      → AdminService.listPayments(status?)
        → PaymentModel.find(status ? { status } : {}).sort({ createdAt: -1 }).exec()
```

### Flow 7: Frontend Routing & Auth Guard

```
  User visits app in browser
      │
      ▼
  main.tsx renders:
    <BrowserRouter>
      <AuthProvider>              ← context provider, holds isAuthenticated + isCheckingAuth
        <AppRoutes />
      </AuthProvider>
    </BrowserRouter>
      │
      ▼
  AuthProvider mounts (useEffect):
    → Calls authService.me() → GET /api/admin/auth/me
    → If 200: set isAuthenticated = true
    → If error (401/network): set isAuthenticated = false
    → Either way: set isCheckingAuth = false
      │
      ▼
  AppRoutes renders:
      │
      ├── /login         → <Login />                   (public — no guard)
      ├── /register      → <Register />                (public — setup instructions, not a signup)
      │
      └── /admin/*       → <ProtectedRoute>            (layout route — auth guard)
            │                 │
            │                 ├── isCheckingAuth = true  → Show "Checking admin session..." spinner
            │                 ├── isAuthenticated = false → <Navigate to="/login" />
            │                 └── isAuthenticated = true  → <AdminLayout> <Outlet /> </AdminLayout>
            │
            └── Nested routes inside <AdminLayout>:
                  ├── index  (/)          → <OverviewPage />   Dashboard
                  ├── /orders             → <OrdersPage />     Order table + filters
                  ├── /products           → <ProductsPage />   Product editor + table
                  └── /payments           → <PaymentsPage />   Payment table
            │
            └── Catch-all (*) → <Navigate to="/admin" />

  AdminLayout shell renders:
    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  SIDEBAR (258px)        │  WORKSPACE                         │
    │                          │  ┌──────────────────────────────┐ │
    │  "WhatsApp Commerce"     │  │  TOPBAR                      │ │
    │  "Admin Panel"           │  │  Page Title (from pathname)  │ │
    │  ──────────────────      │  │  [Refresh] button (reloads)  │ │
    │  📊 Overview  (NavLink)  │  └──────────────────────────────┘ │
    │  📦 Orders    (NavLink)  │                                    │
    │  🏷️ Products  (NavLink)  │  <Outlet />  (page content)       │
    │  💰 Payments  (NavLink)  │                                    │
    │  ──────────────────      │                                    │
    │  Sign Out (calls logout) │                                    │
    └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

