## Complete File Reference

### Backend

| File | Lines | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| `api/index.ts` | ~20 | Vercel serverless handler — lazy-inits Express + MongoDB, caches app across warm starts |
| `src/server.ts` | ~8 | Standalone server entry — `connectToDatabase()` then `app.listen(PORT)` |
| `src/app.ts` | ~25 | Express app factory — `createApp()`: DI container, json middleware, routes at `/api`, static files at `/admin` |
| `src/container.ts` | ~35 | DI container — `ApplicationContainer` class: instantiates all 6 services + 5 controllers, wires dependencies |
| `src/config/env.ts` | ~40 | Loads `.env` via dotenv, exports typed `env` object with 4 sections: `app`, `database`, `whatsapp`, `payment` |
| `src/config/database.ts` | ~5 | `connectToDatabase()` — calls `mongoose.connect(env.database.uri)` |
| `src/models/order.model.ts` | ~80 | Order Mongoose schema + model. Fields: orderReference, customerName, whatsappNumber, sourceMessageId, productName, catalogProductId, quantity, totalAmount, currency, status (enum), paymentStatus (enum), paymentLink, paymentGatewayReference, history (embedded sub-schema, no _id). Exports: `Order`, `OrderDocument`, `OrderModel` |
| `src/models/payment.model.ts` | ~50 | Payment Mongoose schema + model. Fields: orderReference, gatewayReference, amount, currency, status (enum), rawPayload (Mixed). Exports: `Payment`, `PaymentDocument`, `PaymentModel` |
| `src/models/product.model.ts` | ~55 | Product Mongoose schema + model. Fields: name, description, catalogProductId (unique sparse), price, currency, stockQuantity, isActive. Exports: `Product`, `ProductDocument`, `ProductModel` |
| `src/types/order.ts` | ~15 | Shared TypeScript types: `OrderStatus` union, `PaymentStatus` union, `OrderHistoryEntry` interface |
| `src/services/admin-auth.service.ts` | ~91 | `AdminAuthService` — `validateCredentials`, `createSessionToken`, `verifySessionToken`, `createCookie`, `clearCookie`, `extractCookie`, `validateApiKey`, private `sign()` and `safeEqual()` helpers. All comparisons use `crypto.timingSafeEqual`. Session lifetime: 8 hours |
| `src/services/admin.service.ts` | ~62 | `AdminService` — `listOrders(filters)` with status/paymentStatus exact match + search regex $or on orderReference/customerName/whatsappNumber, `getOrder(ref)`, `updateOrderStatus(ref, status, note)` with $push history, `listPayments(status?)` |
| `src/services/order.service.ts` | ~302 | **Core business logic.** `OrderService` — `createFromManualInput`, `handleWhatsAppWebhook`, `handlePaymentWebhook`, private `processMessageValue` (message parsing with fallback chain), `attachPaymentLink`, `createOrder`, `updatePaymentLink`, `updateOrderStatus` (central status update + history $push), `recordPayment` (amount falls back to order → payload → 0), `extractMessageChanges` (flatMap traversal), `buildOrderReference` |
| `src/services/payment.service.ts` | ~29 | `PaymentGatewayService` — `createPaymentLink(payload)`: builds URLSearchParams, HMAC-SHA256 signs with hex digest, appends signature to query |
| `src/services/product.service.ts` | ~60 | `ProductService` — `listProducts`, `createProduct` (with uniqueness check), `updateProduct` (with uniqueness check excluding self), private `ensureUniqueCatalogProductId`. Custom `DuplicateProductCatalogIdError` class |
| `src/services/whatsapp.service.ts` | ~29 | `WhatsAppService` — accepts optional AxiosInstance for DI. `sendTextMessage(to, body)`: POST to Facebook Graph API |
| `src/controllers/admin-auth.controller.ts` | ~40 | `AdminAuthController` — `login` (validates→creates token→sets cookie), `logout` (clears cookie), `me` (returns 200 if middleware passed) |
| `src/controllers/admin.controller.ts` | ~112 | `AdminController` — `listOrders`, `getOrder` (404 if null), `updateOrderStatus` (404 if null), `listPayments`, `listProducts`, `createProduct`, `updateProduct`. Helper methods: `getQueryString` (safe string extraction), `getRouteParam` (handles string|string[]), `handleProductError` (409 for duplicate, 400 otherwise) |
| `src/controllers/health.controller.ts` | ~10 | `HealthController` — `getHealth`: returns `{ success: true, message: "WhatsApp commerce API is running." }` |
| `src/controllers/order.controller.ts` | ~15 | `OrderController` — `createOrder`: calls `OrderService.createFromManualInput(req.body)`, returns 201 |
| `src/controllers/webhook.controller.ts` | ~54 | `WebhookController` — `verifyWhatsAppWebhook` (subscribe+token check→returns challenge or 403), `handleWhatsAppWebhook` (try/catch→200 or 500), `handlePaymentWebhook` (try/catch→200 or 400) |
| `src/middleware/admin-auth.middleware.ts` | ~19 | `requireAdminAuth` factory — takes AdminAuthService, returns middleware that checks cookie session OR x-admin-api-key header |
| `src/routes/index.ts` | ~80 | `createRouter(dependencies)` — single file with all 15 route definitions. Wires each path to its controller method + auth middleware |

### Frontend

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.html` | SPA entry HTML. Title: "WhatsApp Commerce Admin". Loads `/src/main.tsx` as module |
| `src/main.tsx` | React entry point — `<BrowserRouter> <AuthProvider> <AppRoutes />` |
| `src/styles.css` | Custom design system: CSS variables (`--bg`, `--panel`, `--ink`, `--muted`, `--line`, `--teal`, `--amber`, `--red`, `--green`), global base styles for inputs/buttons/tables/labels, `.app-shell` grid layout, `.sidebar`/`.workspace`/`.topbar` layout classes, login panel styles, metrics grid, product editor, table styles, status badges. Responsive: single-column below 920px |
| `src/types.ts` | Frontend types mirroring backend: `OrderStatus`, `PaymentStatus`, `Order`, `Product`, `Payment`, `ProductFormState` |
| `src/auth/AuthProvider.tsx` | React context — `AuthProvider` component + `useAuth()` hook. State: `isAuthenticated`, `isCheckingAuth`. On mount: calls `authService.me()`. Exposes: `login()`, `logout()`, `isAuthenticated`, `isCheckingAuth` |
| `src/auth/Login.tsx` | Login form — pre-filled "admin" username, password input with show/hide toggle, error message display, redirects to `/admin` on success |
| `src/auth/Register.tsx` | Static page — shows instructions for setting `ADMIN_USERNAME`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `ADMIN_SESSION_SECRET` in `.env`. Not a signup form |
| `src/auth/ProtectedRoute.tsx` | Route guard — shows "Checking admin session..." while loading, redirects to `/login` if not authenticated, renders `<Outlet />` if authenticated |
| `src/components/AdminNav.tsx` | Sidebar — brand area ("WhatsApp Commerce" / "Admin Panel"), NavLinks with lucide-react icons (Overview/Orders/Products/Payments), Sign Out button |
| `src/components/MetricCard.tsx` | Dashboard card — `label`, `value`, optional `tone` ("green" | "amber") for left border color |
| `src/components/StatusBadge.tsx` | Pill badge — displays `status` with underscores→spaces, CSS class driven by status value for coloring |
| `src/components/EmptyRow.tsx` | Table empty state — single `<tr>` with `colSpan` and centered message |
| `src/pages/admin/AdminLayout.tsx` | Shell layout — CSS grid (258px sidebar + 1fr workspace). Topbar: page title derived from `location.pathname` + Refresh button (`window.location.reload`). Renders child route via `<Outlet />` |
| `src/pages/admin/OverviewPage.tsx` | Dashboard — `useEffect` fetches orders + products + payments in parallel (`Promise.all`). Computes 6 metrics client-side. Loading/error states handled |
| `src/pages/admin/OrdersPage.tsx` | Orders table — fetches on mount, client-side text filter (searches ref/customer/phone/product) and status dropdown filter. Table columns: Order Ref, Customer, Product, Amount, Status badge, Update dropdown. Each row has a `<select>` to change status |
| `src/pages/admin/ProductsPage.tsx` | Products CRUD — two-column layout: editor form (name, catalogProductId, price, stock, description, isActive checkbox) + product table. Form handles both create and update. Table shows: name, catalog ID, price, stock, Edit button, Publish/Draft toggle |
| `src/pages/admin/PaymentsPage.tsx` | Payments table — fetches on mount. Columns: Order Reference, Gateway Reference, Amount, Status badge, Date |
| `src/routes/AppRoutes.tsx` | Route definitions — `/login`, `/register` (public), `/admin/*` wrapped in `<ProtectedRoute>`, nested index/orders/products/payments routes, catch-all redirect to `/admin` |
| `src/services/api/axiosInstance.ts` | Axios instance — `baseURL: "/api"`, `withCredentials: true`, `headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" }` |
| `src/services/api/authService.ts` | Auth API — `login(username, password)` POST, `logout()` POST, `me()` GET |
| `src/services/api/adminService.ts` | Admin API — `getOrders()` GET, `getPayments()` GET, `getProducts()` GET, `updateOrderStatus(ref, status)` PATCH, `saveProduct(form)` POST or PATCH (determined by `form.id`) |
| `src/utils/formatters.ts` | `money(amount, currency)` — `Intl.NumberFormat("en-PK")` PKR no decimals. `formatDate(value)` — `toLocaleString()` or "-" if falsy |

---

## Key Design Decisions

1. **Cookie + API Key dual auth** — Browsers use `admin_session` HTTP-only cookie; server-to-server uses `x-admin-api-key` header. Both checked by the same middleware function. Either passing grants access.

2. **HMAC-signed sessions (not JWT)** — Custom token format: `base64url(payload).base64url(hmac-sha256)`. Simpler than JWT libraries, same security properties. Uses Node's built-in `crypto` module.

3. **Three sequential WhatsApp notifications on payment** — After payment, the customer gets three messages in sequence (each awaited): payment received → confirmed → processing. Each subsequent message only sends if the previous status update succeeded.

4. **Catalog product ID uniqueness via sparse index** — Products can optionally link to WhatsApp catalog items via `catalogProductId`. The Mongoose `unique: true, sparse: true` index allows multiple `null`/`undefined` values but enforces uniqueness for any non-null value.

5. **Vercel + standalone dual deployment** — The same Express app runs as a Vercel serverless function (`api/index.ts`) or a long-lived Node process (`src/server.ts`). Both share `app.ts` (the app factory) and `container.ts` (the DI wiring).

6. **Single routes file** — All 15 routes are defined in one file ([routes/index.ts](backend/src/routes/index.ts)), making the entire API surface auditable at a glance.

7. **Flexible payment webhook parsing** — `handlePaymentWebhook` tries 3 field names for `orderReference`, 3 for `gatewayReference`, and 2 for `paymentStatus`. This avoids breakage when payment gateway field names vary.

8. **Constant-time credential comparison everywhere** — Every password, API key, and HMAC comparison uses `crypto.timingSafeEqual()`. The `validateCredentials` method also guards against login when `ADMIN_PASSWORD` is not configured.

9. **Manual orders don't send WhatsApp messages** — `createFromManualInput` creates the order + payment link but does NOT notify the customer via WhatsApp. Only orders originating from WhatsApp webhooks get the payment link messaged to the customer.

10. **Admin status updates only change `status`, not `paymentStatus`** — The admin panel can move an order between lifecycle states but only the payment webhook changes `paymentStatus` from `pending` to `paid`/`failed`. This maintains a clear audit trail.

11. **WhatsAppService accepts optional Axios instance** — The constructor takes an optional `httpClient` parameter, allowing test code to inject a mocked Axios instance without hitting the real Facebook Graph API.

12. **No WebSocket or polling** — All communication is request-response via HTTP REST. "Real-time" updates come from WhatsApp and payment gateway webhooks (inbound POST callbacks).
